The paper discusses user authentication in the context of communication channels, which is a topic that falls under information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses security and cryptography, which suggests that it could belong to the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of physical layer authentication (PLA) and channel features also suggests that the paper could belong to the category of multimedia (cs.MM) or networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of keys for authentication, which suggests that it could belong to the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
